Arcane Defiance Armors all contain this same inscription:

"Throughout the realms the wielders of magic are advantaged over the common people. We stand in defiance of their tyranny and casual attitudes to power"

Who we are is unknown, but the protection from magic that these items provide is superior.

The cry of the banshee is a nightmare to most. However, to at least one bardic palemaster from Tarkuul it was beauty. He laboured day and night trying to mimic that dreadful keening but every sword was a failure. They could scream, they could howl but none were perfect. Driven mad by his own failure, he cast the wailing swords to the sea and fell into a deep and profound melancholy that lingers to this day.

Guardians of the Shrine of Eilistraee, these drow are capable warriors.

Fiercely sought after by certain trackers and wardens, these helms possess horn-shaped ear cones that amplify the wearer's hearing tenfold. While the materials used in creation offer little in terms of protection to the face, it offers an unrivaled advantage when it comes to aural detection.

Its a well known fact that elves are foppish gits, barely able to lift their own swords without a limp-wristed floppy motion. It was for this very reason that these boots were forged. 

The master elven smith Yaldriirmathileh Mastiiramaeviil, spent many long hours making these boots for the elven protectors of the long forgotten court of Myth Drannor. When the kingdom fell, many of these boots were lost, some fell into the hands of those responsible for the fall, others are a prized possession from a dragons hoard. 

Perhaps the adventurer who has stumbled upon them now will use them to serve their intended purpose. Perhaps though, they have simply made another step along the road to obscurity.
A polished golden shield set with a large gemstone that seems to act as a third eye for the shield holder, allowing them to see more than most with a conventional tower shield.
The tower shield is a veritable wall of protection, though it can be quite cumbersome to carry on an adventure.

The magically enhanced drow piwafi cloak is one of the most important accoutrements of a drow's possession. Even the most common of these cloaks carries a most powerful enchantment to protect its wearer. All drow long to own a piwafi; though, only those who have proven themselves useful, or who come from rich, powerful families can afford to own one.

Crafted with care by the reclusive and little known sea-elves, these rings are a simple silver band wrought in a somewhat waving pattern, clasping two twin blue pearls. Each pearl is enchanted to help the wearer hear and see in the depths of the murky ocean, as well as the ring itself providing some minor magical fortification.
A copy of an amulet identifying one as Sutrinos, an elite leader of the Melee-Magthere.  These amulets are only worn by commanders that have proven their worth time and time again to the academy.

Before the Underkingdom, also known as "the Spires", fell to the duergar and then to the giants, the once powerful Dwarven Kingdom was known as Dornat Murr.

Among many famous weapons and armors, the dwarven guards wielded doule-sided warhammers. One side flat and able to smash their foe, but a pick on the other side to pierce through even the most sturdy of armors. Feared were those hammers who could wreak doom onto the dwarven foes.

Lucky souls can still rarely find one of those masterpieces of dwarven craftsmenship, scattered all over the isles.

Hardened by the hostile environment, trained extensively and outfitted with high quality equipment, the men and women of the Forrstakkr Guard are a more than capable fighting force in the harsh northern environment. Augmented by veterans from the Ostland conflict, this force is quite ready to protect and fight for the people of Forrstakkr.

Fashioned in the image of the original itself, and enchanted in kind, this staff was modeled after none other than the famous weapon of choice wielded by an icy, cold-hearted tyrant who sourced her spells both from innate talents and old tomes alike. Among other enhancements, those who wield it will note a subtle imperviousness to the cold, and a barely perceptible vulnerability to fire, much like the initial item's first owner.

The Order of the Crouching Lemur are are a monastic group who espouse endurance and strength of spirit in the face of adversity, and prove this by eking out an existence on a harsh mountain in the Skull Crags, beset on all sides by the environment and hostile creatures.

Despite their isolationist ways, they are surprisingly welcoming to outsiders, offering fine wares and supplies to those who can supply the coin. It isn't uncommon to find these robes in place as far as Brogendenstein, and this open nature has helped spread the word of the relatively small monastery across the land.
